 Git & GitHub Note
 What is Git?
Git is a version control system
It helps you track changes in your code

 Simple:

Save versions of your project
Go back to old versions anytime

 Sinhala:

Git කියන්නේ code වෙනස්කම් track කරන system එකක්
 What is GitHub?
GitHub is a website to store Git projects online
It is like cloud storage for code
You can:

Save your project online
Share with others
Work as a team


 Difference Between Git and GitHub
Git	GitHub
Software (installed in PC)	Website
Works offline	Works online
Tracks changes	Stores & shares code
 Basic Git Commands
1. Initialize project
git init

 Start a Git project

2. Add files
git add .

 Add files to staging

3. Commit changes
git commit -m "message"

 Save changes

4. Connect to GitHub
git remote add origin <repo link>
5. Push to GitHub
git push -u origin main

 Upload code to GitHub

6. Clone project
git clone <repo link>

 Download project

 Pull Request (Important 🔥)

 Used when working with others

Steps:

Fork repository
Clone to your PC
Make changes
Push to your repo
Create Pull Request

